## Explanation:

### Solution 01

- Here we’ll take a stack & 2 arrays to solve it.
- We’ll find the left and right smaller of every index and store it in left and right array.
- In the stack, we’ll store the index which is in increasing order for the left array.
- For the right array, we’ll store decreasing indexes in the stack.
- After iterating all elements we’ll calculate the area using **`max(ans, heights[i]*(right[i]-left[i]+1))`**
- **Time complexity:** O(n).

---

## Code:

```cpp
//Solution 01:
**class Solution {
public:
    int largestRectangleArea(vector<int>& heights) {
        int n = heights.size(), ans = 0, left[n], right[n];
        stack<int> st;

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++){
            while(!st.empty() && heights[st.top()] >= heights[i]) st.pop();
            if(st.empty()) left[i]=0;
            else left[i] = st.top() + 1;
            st.push(i);
        }

        while(!st.empty()) st.pop();

        for(int i=n-1; i>=0; i--){
            while(!st.empty() && heights[st.top()] >= heights[i]) st.pop();
            if(st.empty()) right[i] = n-1;
            else right[i] = st.top() - 1;
            st.push(i);
        }

        for(int i=0; i<n; i++)
            ans = max(ans, heights[i]*(right[i]-left[i]+1));

        return ans;
    }
};**
