# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
Just Solve this Problem like any other stack problem of nearest minimum.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
1. Find the nearest minimum elements for the left side of the given array.
2. Find the nearest minimum elements for the right side of the given array. 
3. Find the area of all the elements.
4. For Area you have to find length and breadth is given. So for length just Step 1 stack subtract Step 2 Stack, you will get the length.
5. Then just take the maximum one out and return. 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: N
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: N
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
/**
 * @param {number[]} heights
 * @return {number}
 */
var largestRectangleArea = function(heights) {
    let leftStack = [];
    let stack = [];

//Left side nearest minimum element
    for(let i = 0;i < heights.length;i++){
        while(stack.length !== 0 && heights[stack[stack.length - 1]] >= heights[i]){
            stack.pop();
        }

        if(stack.length === 0){
            leftStack.push(-1);
        }
        else {
            leftStack.push(stack[stack.length - 1]);
        }
        stack.push(i);
    }

//Right side nearest minimum element 
    stack = [];
    let rightStack = [];

    for(let i = heights.length - 1;i >= 0; i--){
        while(stack.length !== 0 && heights[stack[stack.length - 1]] >= heights[i]){
            stack.pop();
        }

        if(stack.length === 0){
            rightStack.push(heights.length);
        }
        else {
            rightStack.push(stack[stack.length - 1]);
        }
        stack.push(i);
    }

    //Calculating maximum  Area 
    let max = -Infinity;
    let area;
    //Area = right - left - 1 (length) * heights[i](breadth)

    for(let i = 0;i < heights.length; i++){
        area = (rightStack[heights.length - i - 1] - leftStack[i] - 1)  * heights[i];
        max = Math.max(area,max);
    }
    return max;
};
```

