# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
what the question asks from us to find the area of maximum rectangle formed by the histograms

how can we find the maximum area by either finding maximum length or maximum breadth..

area=length *breath;
---

here, length of histogram are constant only we can find the maximum breadth for a constant length 
so finding the maximum area we find the maximum area optained from all the lengths with the maximum breadth we found ...

**how to find the maximum breath** 

breadh =n-p-1;
here n= is the next minimum element from the current element
     p=is the previous minimum element from the current element

The million dolloar question arises how to find the next minimum element 
we find this using stack traversing from the back of the array and pops the minimum element if top elemnt is >curr and pushes back if false (see below code )..

similarly while traversing from the front side we find the previous minimum element .




# Approach 1
using stack by finding minimum next and previos value of each element and and finding the maximum in O(n) time comlexity 

there are many other approches also llike left and right array but this is the most optimised one. 

