Intuition behind this algorithm is to first store the index of next smaller element from left(nesL() function do the same) and from right(nseR() function do the same).
Now traverse through each height of the vector and check for the index of next smaller element to the right and index of next smaller element to the left.
maxArea = max(maxArea, ((nseRight[i]-1) - (nseLeft[i]+1) + 1)*heights[i])


for example 
we have a vector of heights = {2, 1, 5, 6 , 2, 3};
so next smaller element index array from right would be {1, 6, 4, 4, 6, 6};
and next smaller element index array from left would be {-1, -1, 1, 2, 1, 4};

now loop through each height and calculate the maxarea from given formula.
and the answer will come out to be 10.

